Canadian gold miner Centerra Gold has completed the sale of its 50% interest in the Greenstone Mines Partnership (GGM) to an affiliate of the Orion Mine Finance Group. Centerra received an upfront cash payment of $210-million for its stake in GGM, which owns the Hardrock project in Ontario. Besides the upfront payment, Centerra is entitled to receive further contingent payments of up to $75-million upon the Hardrock project meeting certain construction or production milestones. Further details can be found in Centerraâ€™s December 15, 2020 news release. Centerra and Premier Gold Mines, which owns the other half of GGM, have locked horns over the development-stage project.